external_knowledge:
-top candidates for tech roles refers to job seekers whose best job matches are in the 'Technology' industry;
-best-matching job details include the job title, location, and industry;
-the match scores represent the compatibility between a job seeker and a job role, with higher scores indicating a better match.

sql:
SELECT job_id
FROM job_matches
WHERE match_score >= 0.7;

external_knowledge:
- Lighthouses represent job postings;
- The bustling harbor symbolizes the location of New York, NY;
- Beacon refers to the salary offered;
- Long-term anchors stand for full-time employment opportunities.

sql:
SELECT title, views
FROM jobs
ORDER BY views DESC;

SELECT title
FROM jobs
WHERE company = 'Example Employer';

SELECT industry, AVG(salary) AS average_salary
FROM jobs
GROUP BY industry;

SELECT COUNT(seeker_id) AS name_count, name
FROM job_seekers
GROUP BY name;
